{"word":"ζηλωτός","slug":"ζηλωτός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ζηλωτός</b></el> <el>(ζηλωτός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ζηλόω'><el>ζηλόω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to be emulated, worthy of imitation</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be deemed happy, to be envied</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of conditions, <i>enviable, blessed</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}